13/08/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- US Ambassador to Athens Thomas Miller assured authorities on Tuesday (12 August) that Washington has no information suggesting an al-Qaeda terrorist presence in Greece. His statement was in response to a recent article in the <I>New York Times </I>, which listed Greece among the countries where al-Qaeda affiliates operate. Miller added that Greece and the United States have so far co-operated very successfully in their common goal of fighting international terrorism. In Washington on Tuesday, State Department spokesman Philip Reeker said there is no data suggesting Greek ties to al-Qaeda in the department's Patterns on Global Terrorism report for 2003. (ANA, MPA - 12/08/03)
